            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJehonadab%2C%20son%20of%20Recab%2C%20was%20quite%20a%20man.%20He%20was%20an%20upstanding%20man%20of%20iron%20principle%20who%20taught%20his%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20the%20precepts%20of%20righteousness.%20His%20biblical%20career%20started%20when%20he%20joined%20Jehu%20in%20destroying%20the%20prophets%20of%20Baal%20(2%20Kings%2010%3A15-17).%20Jehu%20saw%20in%20Jehonadab%20a%20man%20who%20would%20not%20compromise%20with%20Jezebel%20and%20her%20wicked%20prophets%2C%20but%20would%20follow%20through%20in%20delivering%20judgment%20against%20them.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJehonadab%20commanded%20his%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20to%20live%20by%20certain%20standards%20and%20principles%2C%20and%20these%20principles%20were%20still%20being%20upheld%20centuries%20later%20during%20Jeremiah's%20day.%20In%20Jeremiah%2035%3A5-6%2C%20Jeremiah%20offered%20Jehonadab's%20family%20huge%20bowls%20full%20of%20wine%2C%20which%20they%20refused.%20They%20strictly%20maintained%20the%20principles%20of%20purity%20they%20had%20received%20from%20their%20ancestor%20many%20years%20before.%20Jeremiah%20used%20the%20family%20of%20Jehonadab%20as%20a%20perfect%20example%20of%20a%20family%20who%20consistently%20put%20principles%20ahead%20of%20personal%20choice.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20change%20your%20convictions%20because%20they%20don't%20feel%20good.%20King%20Jehoiakim%20just%20took%20a%20knife%20and%20cut%20out%20the%20parts%20of%20the%20Bible%20he%20didn't%20like%20(Jeremiah%2036%3A23)!%20Don't%20change%20your%20Bible%20to%20fit%20your%20lifestyle.%20Change%20your%20lifestyle%20to%20fit%20your%20Bible.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20you'll%20be%20glad%20you%20did!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
